<a name="2088"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Free CES Registration: 30 Days and Counting</div>
<br />
<IMG height=139 src="/print/images/photos/Digital.jpg" width=200 align=right>CES is the trade-only consumer technology event that drives the digital economy. <A href="/register">Act before November 1 to skip the $100 registration fee.</A> <BR><BR>Take note of these important dates and registration fees:<BR>- Before November 1, 2008:&nbsp; $0 <BR>- November 1, 2008: $100<BR>- January 2, 2009: $200<BR>- On-site registration: $200
<P><A href="/print/aboutces.asp">Register now (while it’s free).<BR>Learn more about CES, including show dates and times.<BR></A></P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2087"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Sign up for CES Conference Sessions Now</div>
<br />
<IMG height=125 src="/print/images/photos/p17.jpg" width=165 align=right>Put your thinking caps on. The <A href="/print/sessions/default.asp">2009 CES conference session lineup</A> is here, and it’s time to start filling your schedule with the sessions that will fill your mind with the knowledge you need to succeed in the consumer electronics (CE) industry. <A href="/print/sessions/default.asp">Choose from a variety of session passes</A>, including the All Access Pass and the Ultimate Pass.<BR><BR>The International CES is the consumer technology industry's largest educational forum, featuring more than 200 conference sessions and 500 expert speakers. It’s where to hear about upcoming trends, to understand new technology and to delve deep into technical training. More than 15 partners are poring over material now, prepping to get you in the know.<BR><BR>If you’ve already registered for the 2009 International CES, simply <A href="/register">select the “register” button on CESweb.org</A> again and login with your credentials to pick the conference sessions you want to attend. If you haven’t registered yet, <A href="/register">register for free before November 1</A>, and start picking your sessions now.<BR><BR><STRONG>All Access Pass – Best Value!<BR></STRONG>$1099 advance/$1299 on-site<BR>Includes the entire Ultimate Pass PLUS Billboard’s Digital Music Live!, COMMECTIONS™ Summit, Consumer Electronics Supply Chain Academy, Consumer Robotics Industry Development Program, Flash Memory—The Future of Consumer Products, Fourth Generation Mobile Forum&reg;, Kids@Play, P2P Media Summit LV, Silvers Summit and Understanding Moisture/Reflow Sensitivity for IC Packages. <BR><BR><STRONG>Ultimate Pass <BR></STRONG>Ultimate Pass - $799 advance/$999 on-site <BR>Includes all CES Knowledge Track sessions, Digital Hollywood, Cable Conference at CES, CES Reinventing Advertising, CES Mobile Entertainment and CES Game Power Sessions.&nbsp;&nbsp; <BR>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="2086"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Money-saving Tip: Use the CES Code Word to Get Hotel Discounts</div>
<br />
<IMG height=125 src="/print/images/photos/Strip_165x125.jpg" width=165 align=right>In each issue of CES Up to the Minute, we give you at least one way to save money. Just call us your friendly bottom-line boosters. This time around, learn how dropping the CES name when booking your hotel room saves money  even at such popular resorts as Trump International Hotel and Tower, Palms Casino Resort and Palms Place.<BR><BR>Two popular Las Vegas resorts are now offering <A href="/print/hotelTravel/hotel.asp">official CES rates</A> during show days, January 8-11, 2009. The International CES works with a variety of Las Vegas hotels, including the Palms/Palms Place and the all-new Trump International Hotel and Tower, to offer attendees and exhibitors the lowest rates possible. Additionally, the hotel program allows CES goers to book individual or group reservations. <A href="/print/hotelTravel/hotel.asp">Use the codes featured online at CESweb.org to receive the discounted rates.</A><BR><BR>The Trump International Hotel and Tower is offering CES attendees discounted nightly rates for its studio suites ($365) and one-bedroom suites ($499).&nbsp; Palms is offering $299 nightly rates, while Palms Place is offering $319 for a studio and $499 for a one bedroom suite as of October 1. <BR><BR>Trump International Hotel and Tower is located near all CES venues (1.25 miles from the Las Vegas Convention Center, less than a mile from the Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian). <BR><BR>The Palms features the hottest nightclubs, the coolest pool, world-class dining, state of the art meeting facilities, luxurious rooms and suites, live entertainment and much, much more! Palms Place Hotel and Spa features Simon Restaurant and Bar, a spectacular pool &amp; Drift Spa, a 24-hour room service, Rojo Bar, resort concierge service and a business center. Palms Place has direct access to the Palms Casino Resort via the SkyTubeSM, an elevated, enclosed moving walkway that joins the two complexes. 
